“Pope Francis has decided to announce his decision to convene the Consistory in February in advance so that other meetings that require the participation of cardinals from around the world can be planned,” Lombardi said.
Jack Valero of Catholic Voices said the number of cardinals eligible to vote would likely drop by February.
He explained that a pope usually appoints as many cardinals as necessary so that the number of eligible cardinals is again 120, and as many cardinals over 80 as he wishes.
